---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout>
<main class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center min-h-screen text-white font-mono px-6 text-center">
    <a href="/start" class="absolute top-6 left-6 text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-600 transition-all text-l font-light">
            ‚Üê Back
    </a>
  <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl mb-8 animate-fade-in-slow">Research Focus</h1>
  <p class="max-w-2xl text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed animate-fade-in-slow opacity-80">
    I am fascinated by how memory is <strong class="text-indigo-300">encoded, represented, and traversed</strong> in both human cognition and artificial systems. 
    I focus on <strong class="text-indigo-300">high-dimensional vector spaces of memory, associative memory modeling, and computational architectures</strong> to investigate how both systems navigate and adapt their memory space. 
    By applying various frameworks to bridge neuroscience and AI, I aim to uncover new insights into how <strong class="text-indigo-300">memory structures evolve</strong>,
    and how these processes can inform and advance our understanding of both human cognition and AI.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-12 opacity-70 text-sm">
  </div>

</main>

<style>
.animate-fade-in-slow {
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateY(20px);
  animation: floatFade 2.2s ease forwards;
}
@keyframes floatFade {
  to {
    opacity: 0.8;
    transform: translateY(0);
  }
}

    html, body {
      height: 100%;  
      overflow-y: scroll;  
    }

  body::-webkit-scrollbar {
    display: none;
  }
  body {
    -ms-overflow-style: none;
    scrollbar-width: none;
  }

</style>
</Layout>